@database PopaslClass
@index "Classes.guide/Main"

@Node Main "RxMUI - Popasl Class"


Popasl class    @{"Index" link "Classes.guide/Main"} @{"Super" link "PopstringClass.guide/Main"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The Popasl class is used to create an object made of a string
  object and a button.

  When the button is pressed, an asl.library requester is shown.
  The string contents is set to the selection made in the
  requester.

  Note that a Popasl object has no attribute to specify a key to
  open its requester. It may be specified via Window class
  InputEvent attribute, e.g.
      call Notify("win","InputEvent","ralt f","pop","Open")

  See @{"Popstring" LINK "PopstringClass.guide/Main"}.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Active@{fg text}
  B GN

  @{fg shine}ButtonCycleChain@{fg text}
  B I
  If set to 1, the popup button will be in the window cycle
  chain.

  @{fg shine}IgnorePosition@{fg text}
  B I
  If set to 1, the requester ignores position and
  dimensions.

  @{fg shine}NegativeText@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}NotifyOnlyChanges@{fg text}
  S I
  Normally, the String object would notify NewContenyts anytime
  its Contents changes. This may be changed via AlwaysNotifyNC,
  but when a String object is used as String in a Popasl, it
  notifies its NewContents anytime it changes by default
  (AlwaysNotifyNC=1). Setting this attribute to 0 sets
  AlwaysNotifyNC of the String object to 1. Setting this
  attribute to 1 sets AlwaysNotifyNC of the String object to 0.

  @{fg shine}PopSpec@{fg text}
  M I
  An Image Spec for the pop button

  @{fg shine}PopToFront@{fg text}
  B I
  asl.library V44

  @{fg shine}PositiveText@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}RememberPosition@{fg text}
  B I
  If set to 1, the requester remembers position and
  dimensions.

  @{fg shine}SleepApplication@{fg text}
  B I
  If set 1, the application is put to sleep when the
  requester is active.

  @{fg shine}SleepWindow@{fg text}
  B I
  If set 1, the window is put to sleep when the requester is
  active.

  @{fg shine}String@{fg text}
  S I
  A String class object.

  @{fg shine}String@{fg text}
  S I
  A String class object.

  @{fg shine}Title@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}Type@{fg text}
  S I
  One of:
     o File
     o Font

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}File requester attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}AcceptPattern@{fg text}
  S I
  asl.library V38

  @{fg shine}DoMultiSelect@{fg text}
  B I
  asl.library V38

  @{fg shine}DoPatterns@{fg text}
  B I
  asl.library V38

  @{fg shine}DoSaveMode@{fg text}
  B I
  asl.library V38

  @{fg shine}DrawersOnly@{fg text}
  B I
  asl.library V38

  @{fg shine}FilterMacro@{fg text}
  S I
  At Init time you can define a filter-macro in this attribute:
  anytime the file requester should show an entry, that macro is
  called with 3 arguments:
    1. the name of the entry
    2. the name of the drawer
    3. a pointer to a FileInfoBlock structure relative to the entry

  If the macro fails or returns 1, the entry is showed, otherwise
  the entry is not showed. The macro must be an
  ARexx-in-line-string-macro designed to be fast.
  asl.library V38

  @{fg shine}FilterDrawers@{fg text}
  B I
  asl.library V38

  @{fg shine}Pattern@{fg text}
  S I
  asl.library V36

  @{fg shine}RejectIcons@{fg text}
  B I
  asl.library V38

  @{fg shine}RejectPattern@{fg text}
  S I
  asl.library V38

  @{fg shine}ShowVolumes@{fg text}
  B I
  asl.library V44

  @{fg shine}SortBy@{fg text}
  M ISG
  A number or one of:
     o Date
     o Name
     o Size
  asl.library V44

  @{fg shine}SortDrawers@{fg text}
  M ISG
  A number or one of:
     o First
     o Last
     o Mix
  asl.library V44

  @{fg shine}SortOrder@{fg text}
  M ISG
  A number or one of:
     o Ascend
     o Descend
  asl.library V44

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Font requester attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}BackPen@{fg text}
  N I
  asl.library V36

